fix(test+chore): TLC-034 migration-concurrency advisory lock + TLC-035 .gitattributes EOL normalization (Sprint 19)

Closes two pre-existing main-red issues identified at Sprint 18 retro:

TLC-034 (migration-concurrency flake on parallel test workers):
  Root cause: vitest's `pool: 'forks'` spawns N parallel test-file
  processes; each fork's tests/setup.ts beforeAll calls applyMigrations
  against the shared TEST_DATABASE_URL. Concurrent CREATE FUNCTION /
  CREATE POLICY / CREATE TRIGGER calls update Postgres catalog rows
  (pg_proc, pg_policy, pg_trigger) and Postgres surfaces this as
  "tuple concurrently updated" errors on whichever fork loses the
  race.

  Fix: take a session-scoped pg_advisory_lock keyed on a stable hash of
  'telecheck_test_migrations' before applyMigrations enters its loop;
  release in finally. Only one fork at a time enters the migration-
  apply loop. Other forks block briefly on the lock; when they get
  the lock, the IF NOT EXISTS guards in each migration make their
  applyMigrations a no-op against the already-migrated schema.

  Why advisory lock vs globalSetup refactor: 4-line change vs
  restructuring the whole setup-file architecture. Migrations are
  already idempotent via IF NOT EXISTS guards; serializing the apply
  loop is sufficient to eliminate the catalog race.

  Files: tests/setup.ts (+ ~30 lines, net pg_advisory_lock /
  pg_advisory_unlock pair around the existing apply loop with
  inline rationale comment).

TLC-035 (.gitattributes EOL normalization):
  Root cause: Sprint 18 PR #10 + #12 rebases produced 15 prettier
  "violation" warnings post-rebase that turned out to be EOL-only
  drift (Windows host's `core.autocrlf=true` converts LF → CRLF in
  working copy; LF stored in repo). Without a .gitattributes file,
  every Windows-host autonomous shell rebase risks the same drift
  cycle.

  Fix: NEW .gitattributes with `* text=auto eol=lf` + explicit per-
  extension rules for ts/tsx/js/json/md/yml/yaml/sql/sh + binary
  marker for png/jpg/gif/ico/pdf/zip/gz. Forces LF in repo
  regardless of host OS.

  Files:
    - NEW .gitattributes (~30 lines incl. rationale comment)
    - 14 source files: EOL renormalization (post-renormalize
      git add); content unchanged

Verification:
  - npm run lint clean
  - npx tsc --noEmit clean
  - npm run format:check clean (post-renormalize; ALL files PASS)
  - 14 file modifications post-renormalize are EOL-only; no
    functional changes; git diff with --ignore-all-space confirms
    zero content changes

Sprint 19 commit count: 1 of estimated 3-4 budget (kickoff + this
combined commit + Sprint 19 review/retro). Codex SKIP per §5.2 pure-
chore + test-infra fix (no novel-of-class authoring).

